Package: epb
Title: Enhanced Peters-Belson Method
Version: 0.1.0.9000
Authors@R: person("Josh", "Errickson", email = "josh@errickson.net", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Produces proper estimates in the Enhanced Peters-Belson method; to
    address whether there is an interaction between predicted outcome and treatment.
    This generally arise when testing hypotheses of the form "Do those most at risk
    (predicted to have a low outcome in the absence of treatment) gain more effect
    from the treatment?"
Depends:
    R (>= 3.1),
    sandwich
Imports:
    methods,
    stats
License: GPL-3
LazyData: true
Suggests:
    testthat,
    roxygen2,
    knitr,
    rmarkdown,
    covr
RoxygenNote: 5.0.1
VignetteBuilder: knitr
